details: Learn the fundamentals of the C programming language, including data types, control structures, and memory management.
Explore advanced data structures and algorithms to solve complex computing problems.
Master algorithmic techniques and problem-solving strategies for efficient computation.
Explore object-oriented programming in C++ and develop skills in creating software applications.
Learn Python, a versatile and widely-used programming language, with a focus on object-oriented programming principles.
Master the principles and practices of software engineering, including requirements analysis, design, and testing.
Learn cloud computing using Amazon Web Services (AWS) and deploy scalable and reliable applications.
Master database management and SQL to efficiently store and retrieve data in relational databases.
Develop problem-solving skills and learn algorithmic techniques to tackle complex computational problems.
